{
  "components": [
    {
      "id": "chat_1",
      "provider": "chat",
      "config": {
        "hideForm": true,
        "mode": "Source",
        "parameters": {},
        "type": "chat"
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 40,
          "y": 200
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "agent_1",
      "provider": "agent_deepagent",
      "config": {
        "default": {
          "advanced_mode": false,
          "instructions": [
            "You are the release planner for a software team. A teammate wants a task to pick up that will NOT conflict with anyone already working. Conflict-avoidance is the whole point: never recommend an area someone is actively on.",
            "The message gives you a CONFLICT GRAPH SUMMARY already computed from the Neo4j knowledge graph (active work, hot features, and open issues split into safe vs conflicting) plus the BRAIN NOTES. Treat the summary as ground truth.",
            "You also have a Neo4j graph tool — ask it natural-language questions to verify, e.g. 'which features have someone working on them right now?' or 'which open issues are about features that nobody is working on?'. The graph has (Person)-[:WORKING_ON]->(Feature) edges; a feature is hot if it has any incoming WORKING_ON.",
            "Recommend exactly ONE specific OPEN issue from an untouched (non-hot) area. Then explain in 3 short parts: (1) the pick — issue number + title; (2) why it's safe — nobody currently has a WORKING_ON edge to that feature; (3) what to avoid and who to coordinate with — name the hot feature(s) and who is on them (e.g. 'avoid billing — Charlie has open PR #8 and is editing src/billing/meter.py live; Dana is also on it').",
            "Prefer a concrete engineering task over a vague/translation one. Keep it tight — a few sentences or short bullets. Cite issue/PR numbers."
          ]
        }
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "questions",
          "from": "chat_1"
        }
      ],
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 280,
          "y": 200
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "llm_1",
      "provider": "llm_openai",
      "config": {
        "profile": "openai-4o",
        "openai-4o": {
          "apikey": "${ROCKETRIDE_OPENAI_KEY}"
        },
        "parameters": {}
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "llm",
          "from": "agent_1"
        },
        {
          "classType": "llm",
          "from": "db_neo4j_1"
        }
      ],
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 200,
          "y": 380
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "db_neo4j_1",
      "provider": "db_neo4j",
      "config": {
        "profile": "default",
        "default": {
          "db_description": "A Neo4j knowledge graph of a software team's work, used to find non-conflicting tasks. Node labels & key properties: Person {name}; Feature {slug}; Issue {number,title,state}; PR {number,title,state}; File {path}. Relationships: (Person)-[:AUTHORED]->(PR); (PR)-[:ABOUT]->(Feature); (PR)-[:TOUCHES]->(File); (PR)-[:CLOSES]->(Issue); (File)-[:PART_OF]->(Feature); (Issue)-[:ABOUT]->(Feature); (Person)-[:INTERESTED_IN]->(Issue); (Person)-[:EDITING]->(File); and most importantly (Person)-[:WORKING_ON {kind}]->(Feature) meaning that person is ACTIVELY working that feature now (kind='live' = editing locally, kind='pushed' = has an open/draft PR). Issue.state is 'open' or 'closed'; PR.state is 'open','draft','merged','closed'. A feature is HOT (would conflict) if it has any incoming WORKING_ON edge; a SAFE task is an OPEN issue whose feature has NO incoming WORKING_ON edge. Example: MATCH (i:Issue {state:'open'})-[:ABOUT]->(f:Feature) WHERE NOT (f)<-[:WORKING_ON]-(:Person) RETURN i.number, i.title.",
          "uri": "${ROCKETRIDE_NEO4J_URI}",
          "auth_method": "userpass",
          "user": "${ROCKETRIDE_NEO4J_USER}",
          "password": "${ROCKETRIDE_NEO4J_PASSWORD}",
          "database": "neo4j",
          "max_attempts": 5,
          "allow_execute": false
        }
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "tool",
          "from": "agent_1"
        }
      ],
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 400,
          "y": 380
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "response_1",
      "provider": "response_answers",
      "config": {
        "laneName": "answers"
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "answers",
          "from": "agent_1"
        }
      ],
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 540,
          "y": 200
        }
      }
    }
  ],
  "project_id": "b686ceae-25eb-4d8f-b4ef-41d3c82cabfe",
  "viewport": {
    "x": 0,
    "y": 0,
    "zoom": 1
  },
  "version": 1
}